cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IT, cs.CV, cs.SI 

This paper is primarily focused on machine learning and neural networks, specifically autoencoders. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses optimization and convergence, which suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a possible category. The use of complex numbers and the L2 norm suggests cs.IT (Information Theory) as another possible category. The paper also discusses applications to computer vision (cs.CV) and clustering (cs.SI), which are additional possible categories.
